body_html:
This is most likely a protobuf issue... can you please check the output of the following:

$ python
>>> import google.protobuf.internal.api_implementation as ai
>>> ai.Type()

If this prints 'python' (as opposed to 'cpp') then you probably need to install the fast protobuf library as described here:
https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r0.11/get_started/os_setup.html#protobuf-library-related-issues

body:
This is most likely a protobuf issue... can you please check the output of the following:
```
$ python
>>> import google.protobuf.internal.api_implementation as ai
>>> ai.Type()
```
If this prints `'python'` (as opposed to `'cpp'`) then you probably need to install the fast protobuf library as described here: 
https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r0.11/get_started/os_setup.html#protobuf-library-related-issues
